changeCurrentDesign(25.10)                          changeCurrentDesign(25.10)

Name
       changeCurrentDesign - Changes the partition view

Syntax
       changeCurrentDesign

       [-help]

       [<ptnName>]

       Changes  the  partition  view. It helps you to switch between different
       block cells and get back to the top cell.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes the type  and  default
              information for each changeCurrentDesign parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man changeCurrentDesign

       <ptnName>
              Specifies name of the partition to set as top cell.

              Note:  If  no partition name is specified, then you are taken to
              the top cell of the current design.

              Data_type: string, optional

Examples
              *

                The following commands changes sets tdsp_top as the top cell.

                changeCurrentDesign tdsp_top

Related Information
              * Change Partition View chapter in the Innovus Menu Reference

              * Partitioning the Design chapter in the Innovus User Guide

